The **standard frame rate for traditional animation** (e.g., hand-drawn or cel animation) is **24 FPS**, as established by early film standards to create smooth motion. While higher frame rates (like 30 or 60 FPS) are common in modern video or gaming, 24 FPS remains the classic benchmark for cinematic animation. Some early animations used 12 FPS, but it was too slow for fluid motion.
